{"id":17991,"title":"Protocol for selective growth of Acetobacter pomorum (Ap) and Lactobacillus plantarum (Lp)","title_html":"Protocol for selective growth of Acetobacter pomorum (Ap) and Lactobacillus plantarum (Lp)","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/default_protocol.png"},"doi":"dx.doi.org\/10.17504\/protocols.io.vtfe6jn","doi_status":2,"uri":"protocol-for-selective-growth-of-acetobacter-pomor-vtfe6jn","type_id":1,"published_on":1542881856,"version_id":0,"created_on":1542881225,"categories":null,"creator":{"name":"L\u00facia Serra","affiliation":null,"username":"lcia-serra","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/009.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/009.png"},"badges":[{"id":2,"image":{"source":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg","placeholder":"\/img\/badges\/bronze.svg"},"name":"Author"}],"research_interests":null},"journal":null,"journal_name":null,"journal_link":null,"public":1,"has_versions":0,"link":null,"number_of_steps":5,"authors":[{"name":"L\u00facia Serra","affiliation":"Champalimaud Centre for the Unknown","username":"lcia-serra","link":null,"image":{"source":"\/img\/avatars\/009.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/009.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},{"name":"S\u00edlvia Henriques","affiliation":"Champalimaud Centre for the Unknown","username":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"research_interests":null},{"name":"Carlos Ribeiro","affiliation":"Champalimaud Centre for the Unknown","username":"carlos-ribeiro","link":null,"image":{"source":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/ixff5a6.jpg","placeholder":"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/ixff5a6.jpg"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null}],"versions":[],"groups":[{"id":354,"uri":"ribeiro-lab","title":"Ribeiro Lab","image":{"source":"","placeholder":"\/img\/group_placeholder.png"},"tech_support":{"email":null,"phone":null,"hide_contact":0,"use_email":0},"is_member":0,"request":{"id":354,"flag":0,"is_my":false,"uid":0,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"is_member":0}}],"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"steps":[{"id":684961,"guid":"8BE60210EE3E11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"053C2A0CC0B0491A8B8426E4C9020CCB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"32C96A2F86EB4BBFB9546E1AD5531A4F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">- Inoculate fresh mannitol (200 ml) and MRS (10 ml) media (less than a week old) with a single colony of Ap and Lp, respectively. Incubate Ap at 30 \u00baC, 180 rpm; and Lp at 37 \u00baC, without shaking. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":684962,"guid":"97B6E910EE3E11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","previous_id":684961,"previous_guid":"8BE60210EE3E11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1B56C0332B764D3295AE6542B393DAF2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"CCE9B75621DA4A528BA75CCB5E640F10","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">- Dilute 250 \u00b5l Lp culture in fresh 10 ml MRS media. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Ask for MRS, MRS + Kanamycin (50 \u00b5g\/ml) and MRS + Ampicillin (10 \u00b5g\/ml) plates. The plates should be as fresh as possible - don\u2019t use plates more than one week old. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":684963,"guid":"0A1C7E70EE3F11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","previous_id":684962,"previous_guid":"97B6E910EE3E11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"9FCBCC6D399E4E5CA4EF04A15D23101B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":null}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"4B9F7DA34AEB421F8F174918782E7C6A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">- Measure OD (600 nm) of each culture.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Dilute the highest OD (should be Lp) to the same value of the lowest OD in liquid media.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">For example, if Lp has       an OD of 4.6 and Ap, 0.61, dilute Lp in 1 ml MRS by mixing 132 \u00b5l Lp culture and 868 \u00b5l MRS to obtain cultures with equivalent numbers of Lp and Ap cells. <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">- Prepare adequate Ap and Lp dilutions in PBS 1X and inoculate 50 \u00b5l of each culture (Ap and Lp) in each plate:<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Two MRS plates <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS + Kan plate <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS + Amp plate<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">- Use sterile glass beads to spread the cells and incubate the plates (for 48 hours) as follows: <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS plate at 37\u00baC (optimal growth of Lp) <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS plate at 30\u00baC (optimal growth of Ap) <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">MRS +  Kan plate at 37\u00baC <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">MRS +  Amp plate at 30\u00baC <\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Prepare adequate Ap and Lp dilutions in PBS 1X and inoculate 50 \u00b5l of each culture (Ap and Lp) in each plate:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Two MRS plates <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS + Kan plate <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS + Amp plate<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\"><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">- Use sterile glass beads to spread the cells and incubate the plates (for 48 hours) as follows: <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS plate at 37\u00baC (optimal growth of Lp) <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS plate at 30\u00baC (optimal growth of Ap) <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">MRS +  Kan plate at 37\u00baC <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">MRS +  Amp plate at 30\u00baC <\/li><\/ul><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">- Use sterile glass beads to spread the cells and incubate the plates (for 48 hours) as follows: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS plate at 37\u00baC (optimal growth of Lp) <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">One MRS plate at 30\u00baC (optimal growth of Ap) <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">MRS +  Kan plate at 37\u00baC <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">MRS +  Amp plate at 30\u00baC <\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":684964,"guid":"3770A680EE3F11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","previous_id":684963,"previous_guid":"0A1C7E70EE3F11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D102519CFDE64028A8785948DA1D845B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":null}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"B0C1799E796E4BBF8204E18833628514","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">- Verify if Ap and Lp have grown in the following conditions: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ul style = \"list-style-type:disc;\"><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Ap should only grow in MRS (either 37\u00baC or 30\u00baC) and MRS + Amp <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;list-style-type:disc;\">Lp should only grow in MRS (either 37\u00baC or 30\u00baC) and MRS + Kan<\/li><\/ul><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"},{"id":684965,"guid":"5B86EE80EE3F11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","previous_id":684964,"previous_guid":"3770A680EE3F11E88C89D95BA5ECBEBA","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F377A7022D8640C69B9AEB11B8F1EBFD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054723,"guid":"050E4F5DB8784ABFA5E6DA77A6E83B28","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">For separate plating of Ap and Lp, the same steps are performed, but 50 \u00b5l of each culture are plated in each plate of MRS, MRS + Kan and MRS + Amp, separately. The total number of plates will double.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":null,"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF"}],"materials":[],"description":null}